## Exercise 1 Coefficient Interpretation

**Exercise 1(a)**

- $\hat{\beta}_1$ (fsize) = -0.0412: The Ceteris paribus effect, an increase in household size by one person is associated with a 4.12% (exact is 4.04% so we can just use the approximation)decrease in household income. This is because the dependent variable is in logs and $fsize$ is in levels, so we have a log-level, therefore the correct interpretation uses $\hat{\beta}_1 \times 100$.

- $\hat{\beta}_2$ ($\log(tw)$) = 0.2873: With Ceteris paribus, a 1% increase in household wealth is associated with a 0.2873% increase in household income. Since both the dependent variable and the regressor are in logs log-log, the coefficient is interpreted directly as an elasticity (using $\hat{\beta}_2$)

- $\hat{\beta}_6$ (marr) = 0.4217: Ceteris paribus, households where the main earner is married have approximately 52.46% higher annual household income than those where the main earner is not married. This is calculated using the exact formula $(e^{0.4217} - 1)\times 100 \approx 52.46\%$, as the approximate interpretation using $\hat{\beta}_6 \times 100 = 42.17\%$ is less accurate due to the relatively large coefficient(i.e 0.4217).

**Exercise 1(b)** The model is

$$\log(inc_i) = \hat{\beta}_0 + \hat{\beta}_1 fsize_i + \hat{\beta}_2 \log(tw_i) + \hat{\beta}_3 age_i + \hat{\beta}_4 age_i^2 + \hat{\beta}_5 educ_i + \hat{\beta}_6 marr_i + u_i.$$

The marginal effect of age on $\log(inc)$ is

$$\frac{\partial \log(inc)}{\partial age}
= \hat{\beta}_3 + 2\hat{\beta}_4 \cdot age.$$

Evaluating at $age = 25$:

$$0.0512 + 2(-0.0006)\cdot 25 = 0.0212.$$

Ceteris paribus, at age 25, one additional year of age is associated with approximately a 2.12% increase in annual household income.

For the turning point, we have to set the marginal effect of age = 0: $$\hat{\beta}_3 + 2\hat{\beta}_4 \cdot age^* = 0$$

We rearrange for age and evaluate at the values: $$age^* = -\frac{\hat{\beta}_3}{2\hat{\beta}_4}$$

$$age^* = -\frac{0.0512}{2(-0.0006)} = 42.67$$

Therefore, up until age 42.67 then the income will increase, after this point then it will start to decrease.

